# Checkpoints (large files, generated during training)
transformer/

# Baselines (CNEP/CNMP) packaged datasets + checkpoints, kept on local disk only
baselines/data/*.pickle
baselines/data/*.pickle.bak
baselines/cnep/outputs/
baselines/cnmp/outputs/
# Prediction pickles are small (~90 KB) and useful as reference; keep them tracked.

# Shared source data lives at the repo root in `data/` (consumed by BOTH the
# TP-Transformer pipeline and the baseline dataset builder).
#
# `data/processed/` (~6.5 MB of small CSVs/H5s + action_summary.pickle) is
# committed so the teammate gets it on `git clone`.
#
# `data/raw/cnep_action_*/` is the full 2 GB demo bundle (every stereo frame +
# raw trajectory CSV). We commit ONLY the first-frame `0_left.png` per demo
# (~143 MB, 88 files) so the teammate can see what each scene looks like and
# can run `prepare_baseline_dataset.py` end-to-end. Everything else under
# `cnep_action_*/<demo>/` (other PNGs, the raw CSV) is ignored and lives on
# the lab shared drive only.
data/raw/cnep_action_*/*/*
!data/raw/cnep_action_*/*/0_left.png

